OL,3,CMan who served 36 years in jail for
OL,4,Cmurder to have case reviewed
OL,6,FBut he has always maintained his
OL,7,Finnocence, despite it costing him an
OL,8,Fextra 20 years in prison because of
OL,9,Fhis refusal to confess to a Parole
OL,10,FBoard.
OL,12,FAfter several attempts to clear his
OL,13,Fname Mr Gilbert has now received a
OL,14,Fletter from the Criminal Cases Review
OL,15,FCommission (CCRC) confirming it is
OL,16,Freviewing his case and will decide
OL,17,Fwhether to refer it for an appeal.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
