OL,3,CMan who served 36 years in jail for
OL,4,Cmurder to have case reviewed
OL,6,FMr Gilbert, who was aged 22 at the
OL,7,Ftime of his arrest, initially admitted
OL,8,Fthe crime - but says he was coerced
OL,9,Fand threatened into confessing during
OL,10,F48-hours of police questioning staged
OL,11,Fwithout legal representation or an
OL,12,Fappropriate adult.
OL,14,FSince conviction, he has consistently
OL,15,Fprotested his innocence.
OL,17,FIf his latest attempt to overturn his
OL,18,Fconviction is successful, he will be
OL,19,Fone of the UK's longest ever
OL,20,Fmiscarriage of justice victims.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
