OL,3,CMan who served 36 years in jail for
OL,4,Cmurder to have case reviewed
OL,6,FShe said: "Ray was vulnerable when he
OL,7,Fwas questioned. I think the police may
OL,8,Fhave been aware... and he's ended up
OL,9,Fconfessing to a crime that I don't
OL,10,Fthink he did.
OL,12,F"The details in his confessions don't
OL,13,Fmatch what I'm seeing at the crime
OL,14,Fscene.
OL,16,F"Every time Ray's applied to the CCRC,
OL,17,Fthey have said there's no new
OL,18,Fevidence. But this time, I'm offering
OL,19,Fa brand new argument."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
