OL,3,CMan who served 36 years in jail for
OL,4,Cmurder to have case reviewed
OL,6,F"On the run up to Ray's arrest - eye
OL,7,Fwitnesses described the attackers, or
OL,8,Fthose trying to gain access to the
OL,9,Fbuilding as being white men, and then
OL,10,Fonce Ray was arrested, witnesses were
OL,11,Fthen saying they were mixed race."
OL,13,FShe added: "I really hope this time
OL,14,Fthe CCRC will listen and that they'll
OL,15,Fat least do a forensic review of any
OL,16,Fremaining samples.
OL,18,F"If Ray's case does get referred to
OL,19,Fthe court of appeal - then this could
OL,20,Fbe one of the longest miscarriages of
OL,21,Fjustice known in the UK."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/8
